article.headline: Chicago St 81, Southern Utah 68
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Craig Franklin scored 24 points to lead Chicago St. to an 81-68 win Thursday night over Southern Utah. Franklin was one of three Cougars in double-digits, followed Royce Parran with 16 and Marin Mulic and Tony Weeden with 12 each. The Cougars (5-13, 4-4 Mid-Continent) took a 39-30 lead into the half and outscored Southern Utah (10-11, 3-7 Mid-Continent) in the second half with 26-of-56 shooting from the field. DeAngelo Newsom led Southern Utah with 21 points, helped by Lubor Olsovsky with 13 and Jason Baker with 12.
